A: The issue is with this line:
names.add(dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator().next().getValue(String.class));

You're creating a new iterator for each child in the loop, so you're always adding the first child's value to the list.
Instead, you should create the iterator outside of the loop and use it to get the values:
Iterator<DataSnapshot> it = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator();
while(it.hasNext()) {
    names.add(it.next().getValue(String.class));
}

This way, you're using the same iterator to get all the values, and you'll get all of them.

